Close is the sixth studio album by Kim Wilde, released in 1988. 

Produced by Ricky Wilde and Tony Swain, Close was the final album on Which Marty Wilde had co-writer credits. The album is widely perceived By fans and critics (and Kim herself) as Wilde&amp;#039;s most well-balanced, with many kinds of pop represented: dance, ballad, rock and midtempo. 
